   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# STEP B - Feature selection supervised"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "4eabba82",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Extract target \n",
    "The `Target` is the diagnosis of heart disease, the original variable name is `num`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "b715ba9e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "y = dataset[\"target\"]\n",
    "# convert to binary classification\n",
    "y = (y>0).astype(int)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b91e9a2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Train -test split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "afb88feb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# import function to split dataset into training and testing sets\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X_encoded, y,\n",
    "    test_size=0.2,\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    stratify=y\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5b22618f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## ANOVA F-Test (Univariate)\n",
    "For **Univariate method** we will use **ANOVA F-test**  selected the most relevant features based on their statistical relationship with the target variable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "b548c477",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "Selected features (ANOVA):\n",
      "Index(['age', 'trestbps', 'chol', 'thalach', 'oldpeak', 'ca', 'sex_1', 'cp_2',\n",
      "       'cp_3', 'cp_4', 'fbs_1', 'restecg_1', 'restecg_2', 'exang_1', 'slope_2',\n",
      "       'slope_3', 'thal_6', 'thal_7'],\n",
      "      dtype='object')\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Import feature selection tools/library\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif\n",
    "\n",
    "k = 'all'\n",
    "\n",
    "selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=k)\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train_kbest = selector.fit_transform(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "X_test_kbest = selector.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "selected_kbest = X_encoded.columns[selector.get_support()]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nSelected features (ANOVA):\")\n",
    "print(selected_kbest)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ebf683fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6522b865",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The selected features include both numerical variables (such as thalach, oldpeak, and ca) and encoded categorical variables (such as cp, exang, and thal). These variables are clinically meaningful and are known to be strong indicators of heart disease.\n",
    "\n",
    "For instance, ST depression (oldpeak) and the number of major vessels (ca) are key diagnostic indicators, while maximum heart rate (thalach) reflects cardiovascular performance. The inclusion of categorical features such as chest pain type and exercise-induced angina further supports the model's ability to distinguish between patients with and without heart disease."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9f4b94b4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## F-Scores"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c53a9a93",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# creation of a dataframe with feature names and their F-score\n",
    "anova_results = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"feature\": X_encoded.columns,\n",
    "    \"F_score\": selector.scores_\n",
    "}).sort_values(by=\"F_score\", ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFeature ranking:\")\n",
    "print(anova_results)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7301a645",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# plot \n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sort features (lowest → highest for better visualization)\n",
    "anova_results_sorted = anova_results.sort_values(by=\"F_score\", ascending=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.barh(anova_results_sorted[\"feature\"], anova_results_sorted[\"F_score\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Feature Importance (ANOVA F-test)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"F-score\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Features\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ad1bc325",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The results show that features such as **thal_7.0**, **cp_4.0**, and **ca** have the highest F-scores, indicating strong discriminatory power.\n",
    "\n",
    "In particular, thalassemia status (thal) and chest pain type (cp) emerge as the most influential categorical variables, while the number of major vessels (ca) is a key clinical indicator. Additional variables such as exercise-induced angina (exang), maximum heart rate (thalach), and ST depression (oldpeak) also show substantial importance.\n",
    "\n",
    "Conversely, variables such as cholesterol (chol), resting blood pressure (trestbps), and fasting blood sugar (fbs) exhibit low F-scores, suggesting limited contribution to class separation in this dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "The plot confirms that a subset of features carries most of the predictive information, supporting the use of feature selection to reduce dimensionality while preserving interpretability."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "be97cb90",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Wrapper Method (Multivariate)\n",
    "### Forward feature selection  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3810946f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import wrapper libraries and model\n",
    "from sklearn.feature_selection import SequentialFeatureSelector\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# define model used to evaluate feature subsets\n",
    "model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)\n",
    "\n",
    "# initialize sequential feature selector\n",
    "sfs = SequentialFeatureSelector(\n",
    "    model,                        # model used to evaluate feature subsets\n",
    "    n_features_to_select=k,       # number of features to select\n",
    "    direction=\"forward\",          # start with no features and add one by one\n",
    "    scoring=\"accuracy\",           # evaluation metric\n",
    "    cv=5,                         # 5-fold cross-validation\n",
    "    n_jobs=1                       # all available CPU cores\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# fit forward selection on training data\n",
    "sfs.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "# get selected feature names\n",
    "selected_sfs = X_encoded.columns[sfs.get_support()]\n",
    "\n",
    "# print selected features\n",
    "print(\"\\nSelected features (Forward Selection):\")\n",
    "print(selected_sfs)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "51015ee9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create DataFrame from wrapper results\n",
    "wrapper_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"Feature\": X.columns,\n",
    "    \"Selected\": X.columns.isin(selected_sfs).astype(int)\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Keep only selected features\n",
    "selected_wrapper_df = wrapper_df[wrapper_df[\"Selected\"] == 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot\n",
    "plt.figure()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.barh(selected_wrapper_df[\"Feature\"], selected_wrapper_df[\"Selected\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Selected Features (Forward Selection)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Selected (1 = Yes)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Features\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6e7aba1a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Comparison between ANOVA and Wrapper Method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "76fee877",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "comparison_df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "    \"Feature\": X.columns,\n",
    "    \"ANOVA\": X.columns.isin(selected_kbest).astype(int),\n",
    "    \"Wrapper\": X.columns.isin(selected_sfs).astype(int)\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "comparison_df.set_index(\"Feature\").plot(kind=\"bar\", figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Feature Selection Comparison\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Selected (1 = Yes)\")\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=90)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0ab21fc8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- Some features are consistently selected by both methods, indicating strong relevance, while others differ due to the wrapper method’s ability to capture interactions between variables.\n",
    "- Many features were consistently selected by both methods, including `thalach`, `ca`, `cp_4.0`, and `thal_7.0`, indicating that these variables have strong predictive power and a stable relationship with the target variable. The agreement between methods increases confidence in their relevance.\n",
    "\n",
    "- However, some features were selected by only one method. For example, ANOVA selected features such as exang_1.0 and slope_2.0, while the wrapper method selected features like cp_2.0 and fbs_1.0. This difference arises because ANOVA evaluates each feature independently, while forward selection considers interactions between features within a predictive model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d355d6b3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Final Feature set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "29ffb9ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#  FINAL FEATURE SET (ANOVA)\n",
    "X_selected = X_encoded[selected_kbest]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFinal feature shape:\", X_selected.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "# SCALE FINAL FEATURES\n",
    "scaler_final = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_selected_scaled = scaler_final.fit_transform(X_selected)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ee32db10",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## # Export selected features dataset to CSV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "038d886a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "import joblib\n",
    "\n",
    "output_dir = Path(\"../data/03_selected\")\n",
    "output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Original selected\n",
    "X_selected_original = X_selected.copy()\n",
    "X_selected_original[\"target\"] = y.values\n",
    "\n",
    "X_selected_original.to_csv(\n",
    "    output_dir / \"selected_features_original.csv\",\n",
    "    index=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Scaled selected\n",
    "X_selected_scaled_df = pd.DataFrame(\n",
    "    X_selected_scaled,\n",
    "    columns=X_selected.columns\n",
    ")\n",
    "X_selected_scaled_df[\"target\"] = y.values\n",
    "\n",
    "X_selected_scaled_df.to_csv(\n",
    "    output_dir / \"selected_features_scaled.csv\",\n",
    "    index=False\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save scaler\n",
    "joblib.dump(scaler_final, output_dir / \"scaler.pkl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
